FLOODS have left at least five people dead in northern Mozambique. More than 50 people have been injured and over 1 100 houses destroyed in Cabo Delgado, Nampula, Tete and Zambezia provinces. The total population directly affected is estimated at 10 000 people. A key bridge over, Montepuez River, has been washed away, cutting off access to 11 districts. Mozambique is experiencing above-normal rainfall, causing flooding in the north. Rains and flooding are expected to continue throughout the week.â€“ CAJ NEWS